{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17588524","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17588524"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:09:45+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:09:45+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15163"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15163","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15163"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.03,0,0.93,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7854"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66772"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7854","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7854"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15163"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52226"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"112"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"8131"},{"type":"tags","id":"8136"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19149"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19151"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22319"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66772","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66772"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThere have been considerable advances in robotic surgery over the last decade. It is used across a number of disciplines, including orthopaedics, cardiac and general surgery.  Use of robotics allows many types of complex procedures to be performed with more precision, flexibility and control than is possible with traditional approaches. One area where it has seen considerable use is urology.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst it has considerable advantages over conventional approaches for prostate cancer surgery, robotic surgery does have its limitations.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most significant limitation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Higher intraoperative blood loss","Longer patient recovery time","Reduced number of cases per operating session","High equipment and maintenance costs","Poorer visualisation of surgical field"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigh equipment and maintenance costs\u003C/strong\u003E are the most significant limitation of robotic surgery compared to conventional approaches. The initial investment in robotic systems is substantial, and ongoing costs for maintenance and training further add to the financial burden. Despite these costs, robotic surgery offers similar clinical outcomes to conventional laparoscopic surgery for prostate cancer.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigher intraoperative blood loss\u003C/strong\u003E is not typically associated with robotic surgery. In fact, robotic surgery often results in less blood loss due to its precision and enhanced visualisation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELonger patient recovery time\u003C/strong\u003E is not a limitation of robotic surgery. Recovery times are generally comparable to or even shorter than those for conventional laparoscopic surgery due to the minimally invasive nature of the procedure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduced number of cases per operating session\u003C/strong\u003E can be a consideration due to the time required for setup and operation of robotic systems. However, this is not as significant a limitation as the costs involved.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPoorer visualisation of surgical field\u003C/strong\u003E is not a limitation of robotic surgery. In fact, one of the main advantages of robotic systems is the enhanced 3D visualisation they provide, which can improve surgical precision.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Robotic surgery has higher initial and ongoing costs compared to conventional laparoscopic surgery, including equipment, maintenance, and training.","Despite higher costs, robotic surgery shows similar clinical outcomes to conventional laparoscopic surgery for most gastrointestinal procedures.","The main advantages of robotic surgery are improved ergonomics for surgeons and enhanced 3D visualisation of the surgical field."],"references":["Rivero-Moreno Y, Echevarria S, Vidal-Valderrama C, Pianetti L, Cordova-Guilarte J, Navarro-Gonzalez J, Acevedo-Rodr\u00edguez J, Dorado-Avila G, Osorio-Romero L, Chavez-Campos C, Acero-Alvarrac\u00edn K. Robotic Surgery: A Comprehensive Review of the Literature and Current Trends. Cureus. 2023 Jul 24;15(7):e42370. doi: 10.7759/cureus.42370. PMID: 37621804; PMCID: PMC10445506.","Lantz A, Bock D, Akre O, Angenete E, Bjartell A, Carlsson S, Modig KK, Nyberg M, Kollberg KS, Steineck G, Stranne J, Wiklund P, Haglind E. Functional and Oncological Outcomes After Open Versus Robot-assisted Laparoscopic Radical Prostatectomy for Localised Prostate Cancer: 8-Year Follow-up. Eur Urol. 2021 Nov;80(5):650-660. doi: 10.1016/j.eururo.2021.07.025. Epub 2021 Sep 15. PMID: 34538508.","Li JK, Tang T, Zong H, Wu EM, Zhao J, Wu RR, Zheng XN, Zhang H, Li YF, Zhou XH, Zhang CC, Zhang ZL, Zhang YH, Feng WZ, Zhou Y, Wang J, Zhu QY, Deng Q, Zheng JM, Yang L, Wei Q, Shen BR. Intelligent medicine in focus: the 5 stages of evolution in robot-assisted surgery for prostate cancer in the past 20 years and future implications. Mil Med Res. 2024 Aug 21;11(1):58. doi: 10.1186/s40779-024-00566-z. PMID: 39164787; PMCID: PMC11337898."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"it